                <h1>‘The Lighthouse’ is a darkly funny and harrowing examination of masculinity</h1>
                                    <h2>movie review</h2>
                
                                    <figure class="dom-art-container my-4">
                                                    <img src="https://snworksceo.imgix.net/dtc/77de3703-113b-475d-9150-97c5f5abc2d8.sized-1000x1000.jpg?w=1000" alt="&#x201C;The&#x20;Lighthouse&#x201D;&#x20;is&#x20;a&#x20;tempest&#x20;in&#x20;a&#x20;bottle,&#x20;a&#x20;carefully&#x20;calibrated&#x20;psychological&#x20;thriller&#x20;posing&#x20;as&#x20;if&#x20;it&#x20;is&#x20;out&#x20;of&#x20;control." class="w-100">
                                                <div class="domphoto-caption mt-2 text-left text-md-right">
                            “The Lighthouse” is a tempest in a bottle, a carefully calibrated psychological thriller posing as if it is out of control.

                                                             <aside class="photo-caption photo-credit d-block pl-1">
                                    <figcaption class="d-block">
                                                                                    Photo by <a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/staff/courtesy-of-a24">Courtesy of A24</a> |
                                                                                                                                The Chronicle
